    <body>
      <div xml:id="NA236-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">itu talaimakaṉ ciṟaippuṟamāka vaṟpuṟukkun tōḻikkut talaimakaḷ colliyatu.</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">This is what SHE said to the confidante who was consoling [her] when HE was behind the fence.</p>
        </div>
      <div xml:id="NA236">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>            nōyuṅ kaimmikap peritē meyyun</l>
<l>            tīyumiḻ teṟaliṉ veytā kiṉṟē</l>
<l>            yoyyeṉac ciṟitāṅ kuyiriyar paiyeṉa</l>
<l>            muṉṟiṟ koḷiṉē nantuvaḷ periteṉa</l>
<l>            niraiya neñcat taṉṉaik kuyttāṇ </l>
<l>            ṭuraiyiṉi vāḻi tōḻi puraiyi</l>
<l>            ṉuṇṇē relvaḷai ñekiḻttōṉ kuṉṟat</l>
<l>            taṇṇa ṉeṭuvarai yāṭit taṇṇeṉa</l>
<l>            viyalaṟai mūḻkiya vaḷiyeṉ</l>
<l>            pacalai yākan tīṇṭiya ciṟitē.</l>
            </lg>
        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>Exceedingly great [is] the pain and my body</l>
<l>has become hot as if being shot [and] scorched by fire.</l>
<l rend="indent3">“If I take [her] to the front yard, gently, so that she</l>
<l rend="indent3">breathes there a little, deeply(?), she will flourish<note place="foot">Note here the curious double connotation of nantu which can mean either "to flourish" or "to perish". The implication of this is presumably that if HE will not come soon in person to relieve HER, she will perish, wind or no.</note>,”</l>
<l>[thus] tell now, oh friend,</l>
<l rend="indent">to mother with [her] heart of hell, after having sent [me] there</l>
<l rend="indent3">– so that the wind diving between the wide rocks</l>
<l rend="indent3">cooly [and] playing on the superior long mountain</l>
<l rend="indent">in the hills of him who loosened my defectless<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">puraiyil</term>: "defectless" seems pretty straightforward; curiously enough the interpretation given by T.V.G. here is "without holes".</note> fine fine bangles,</l>
<l rend="indent2">will grip for a little [while] my pallorous bosom.</l>
    </lg>
      </div>
